==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|spede||prosperity, good luck, quickness, success|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|sped|spēd|luck, prosperity, success|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|spōdiz||spēdiz|prosperity, success|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Germanic|spōwanan|to prosper, succeed, be happy|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|spē-/*sphē-|to prosper, turn out well|lang=en}}.  Cognate with {{nl}} {{term|spoed||speed|lang=nl}}, {{de}} {{term|sputen||to speed|lang=de}}, {{ang}} {{term|spowan|spōwan|to be successful, succeed|lang=ang}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/spiːd/}}
* {{audio|en-us-speed.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|iːd}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# the state of moving quickly or the capacity for rapid motion; [[rapidity]]
# the rate of motion or action, specifically {{math}}/{{physics}} the magnitude of the [[velocity]]; the rate [[distance]] is traversed in a given [[time]]
# {{photography}} the sensitivity to light of [[film]], [[plates]].  <!--, etc.; [[shutter speed]] -->
# {{slang}} any [[amphetamine]] drug used as a [[stimulant]], especially illegally, especially [[methamphetamine]]
# {{archaic}} luck, success, prosperity

